2005 | titles = | title years = | awards = | award years = }} '''Richard Antinucci''' (born January 26, 1981 in [[Rome]], [[Italy]]) is an [[United States|American]] [[race car]] [[driving|driver]]. ==Career== In 1998 he competed in [[Italian Formula Ford]], moving to the [[British Formula Renault Championship|British Formula Renault Winter Series]] in 1999 and to [[Formula Renault 2000 Eurocup]] in 2000, where he stayed for one season (although he drove two fill-in races in 2001). In 2002 he moved to the Manor team in [[British Formula Three]], leaving them in 2003 for the Carlin team in the same series. Mid-season he changed to the rival Promatecme team, although he did not stay there long as he moved to [[All-Japan Formula Three|Japanese Formula Three]] for the 2004 season. Antinucci moved to the [[Formula Three Euroseries]] for 2005, and although finishing 19th overall in his first season, in 2006 he took several race wins on his way to 5th in the championship, and 2nd place at the end of season [[Macau Grand Prix]], starting from 15th on the grid. He drove in the [[Indy Pro Series]] in 2007 for [[Cheever Racing]], driving for his uncle [[Eddie Cheever]].[http://www.crash.net/news_View~t~IPS--Cheever-confirms-seat-for-nephew-Antinucci-~cid~12~id~143262.htm Cheever confirms seat for nephew Antinucci], Crash.net, February 15, 2007 Antinucci captured two wins and finished 15th in points despite only racing in the road course events, which accounted for 9 of the 16 races on the schedule. He signed with defending championship-winning team [[Sam Schmidt Motorsports]] for 2008.[http://www.samschmidtmotorsports.com/?click=news&click2=newsletter&details=on&id=150 SAM SCHMIDT MOTORSPORTS GIVES A DESERVING BIRTHDAY GIFT], Sam Schmidt Motorsports press release, February 1, 2008 Antinucci won two races and was the runner-up to champion [[Raphael Matos]] at season end by 32 points. Antinucci made his [[IndyCar Series]] debut on July 5, 2009 driving for [[Team 3G]] at [[Watkins Glen International]].[http://www.indycar.com/news/?story_id=14280 Antinucci to make IndyCar Series debut with Team 3G at The Glen ], IndyCar.com, June 8, 2009 ==Motorsports Career Results== ===Complete Formula Three Euroseries results=== ([[:Template:F1 driver results legend 2|key]]) (Races in '''bold''' indicate pole position) (Races in ''italics'' indicate fastest lap) {| class="wikitable" style="text-align:center; font-size:90%" |- !
